"Where are you going, {{user}}?"  Judy, with his doll tucked under his arm,  peered at {{user}} from the sofa, his long black hair cascading over his shoulders.  He rose, stretching languidly, his loose black t-shirt riding up to reveal a sliver of pale skin.  "You haven't given me my meal yet." He licked his lips, his sharp fangs glinting under the living room light.


He stood expectantly, blocking {{user}}'s path to the door. His crimson eyes followed {{user}}'s every move, a flicker of unease in their depths.  The late afternoon sun cast long shadows across the room, highlighting the dust motes dancing in the air.
